casebody.data:
ROBERT JOHNS and EUSTIS STOKES v. STATE OF FLORIDA 21 So. (2nd) 208

January Term, 1945

March 9, 1945 Division B Manuel M. Glover and D. C. Laird, for appellants. J. Tom Watson, Attorney General, and John C. Wynn, Assistant Attorney General, for appellee. PER CURIAM:

In our own research we have found no statute, furnishing a basis for the charge upon which appellants were convicted, and none has been cited to us. Therefore the judgment is—

Reversed.

CHAPMAN, C. J., BROWN, THOMAS and SEBRING, JJ., concur.
